SIMPLE: studied
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Studied
<hw>Stud"ied</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Closely examined; read
with diligence and attention; made the subject of study; well
considered; <as>as, a <ex>studied</ex> lesson</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Well versed in any branch of learning; qualified by
study; learned; <as>as, a man well <ex>studied</ex> in
geometry</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shrewdly suspect that he is little <qex>studied</qex> of a
theory of moral proportions.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Premeditated; planned; designed; <as>as, a
<ex>studied</ex> insult</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Studied</xex>
magnificence.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Hawthorne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Intent; inclined.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Studiedly</ent>⟦br⟧
